          <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; margin-top: 1rem;">
            <button type="button" id="copy-active-btn" class="calc-btn" style="flex: 1.2; height: 42px; font-size: 0.85rem;">Copy Post Content</button>
            <button type="button" id="clear-sandbox-btn" class="calc-btn-secondary" style="flex: 0.8; height: 42px; font-size: 0.85rem;">Clear</button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div slot="about" class="editorial-content">
    <h2>Threads Hashtag Generator: Optimize Topic Tags & Post Spacing</h2>
    <div style="margin: 1.5rem 0; background: var(--color-bg-alt); padding: 1.25rem; border-radius: var(--radius-md); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-left: 4px solid var(--color-brand);">
      <p style="margin: 0; font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        🧵 <strong>Looking to maximize engagement on the Threads app?</strong> Read our comprehensive strategy guide on <a href="/blog/threads-hashtag-generator-guide" style="color: var(--color-brand); text-decoration: underline;">Threads Hashtags & Spacing Rules</a> to learn how to write compelling social copies, select relevant tags, and index in search feeds.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h3>Introduction</h3>
    <p>
      Threads, the text-based social conversation platform built by Instagram, allows creators and brands to share text updates, links, photos, and videos. To make posts discoverable in user searches, Threads supports clickable topic tags. This free <strong>threads hashtag generator</strong> helps you quickly identify relevant tags for your post topic while keeping track of the strict character limits.
    </p>

    <h3>How to Use This Tool</h3>
    <p>
      To write formatted Threads posts with optimized keyword tags, follow these instructions:
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Define Topic:</strong> Input your target post topic or draft context (e.g. "morning productivity tips", "healthy cooking hacks").</li>
      <li><strong>Select Category:</strong> Choose from the 26 supported conversation niches.</li>
      <li><strong>Select Quantity:</strong> Pick how many tags you want to append, with support for 1, 3, 5, or 10 tags.</li>
      <li><strong>Generate Post:</strong> Click <strong>Generate Tags</strong> to draft a copy and select relevant hashtags.</li>
      <li><strong>Sandbox Edit:</strong> Customize the post in the active sandbox workspace, watch the character limits progress bar (optimal under 500 characters), and copy your finished post.</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>What is Threads Hashtag Generator</h3>
    <p>
      A <strong>threads hashtag generator</strong> or <strong>threads tag generator</strong> is a digital helper designed to create search-optimized posts. It matches post topics with relevant conversation keywords, turning text drafts into clickable Threads-compliant posts.
    </p>

    <h3>How Does It Work?</h3>
    <p>
      The generator uses a metadata tag database to pair keywords with categories:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Database matching:</strong> Pulls from a curated seed database of tags categorized by niches (decor, food, crafts, travel).</li>
      <li><strong>Relevancy weighting:</strong> Filters tags by search volume based on your style choice (narrow vs broad).</li>
      <li><strong>Audit tools:</strong> Measures description character lengths (max 500) and counts total tags (recommends 2-5 tags).</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Example Calculation</h3>
    <p>
      Let's look at how a Threads post character budget is allocated:
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Input Parameters:</strong><br />
      ✦ Topic: "productivity habits"<br />
      ✦ Target Count: 3 tags<br />
      ✦ Base Draft: "Establish a simple morning routine to start your workday with high energy and focus." (91 characters)
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Hashtags Budget Allocation:</strong><br />
      ✦ Generated tags: `#productivity #habits #focus` (28 characters).<br />
      ✦ Total Post character length: `91 + 28 = 119 characters`.<br />
      ✦ Threads Limit Check: Since 119 is well under the 500 character limit, the text will display cleanly without getting cropped. The 3 hashtags fall within the recommended limit.
    </p>

    <h3>Who Should Use This Tool?</h3>
    <p>
      This <strong>free threads keyword tool</strong> is designed for:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Creators & Influencers:</strong> Driving conversational reach to build their follower base.</li>
      <li><strong>Blogger & Writers:</strong> Sharing text snippets that link back to articles.</li>
      <li><strong>Social Media Managers:</strong> Writing high-volume scheduling templates for Threads.</li>
      <li><strong>Brands & Marketers:</strong> Tagging sponsored conversations to rank in trending discussions.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</ToolLayout>

